DeviantArt.label: deviantART, Inc.
DeviantArt.description: DeviantArt, LLC is an online community showcasing various forms of user-made artwork. It was first launched on August 7, 2000 by Scott Jarkoff, Matthew Stephens, Angelo Sotira and others. Wikipedia
DeviantArt.Founded: August 7, 2000, Los Angeles, California, United States

Google Search.label: Google
Google Search.description: Google is an American multinational corporation specializing in Internet-related services and products. These include search, cloud computing, software, and online advertising technologies. Most of its profits are derived from AdWords. Wikipedia
Google Search.Founded: September 4, 1998, Menlo Park, California, United States

Galaxy Zoo.label: Galaxy Zoo
Galaxy Zoo.description: Galaxy Zoo is an online astronomy project which invites people to assist in the morphological classification of large numbers of galaxies. Wikipedia

FeedBurner.label: FeedBurner
FeedBurner.description: FeedBurner is a web feed management provider launched in 2004. FeedBurner was founded by Dick Costolo, Eric Lunt, Steve Olechowski, and Matt Shobe. Costolo, a University of Michigan graduate, became CEO of Twitter in 2010. Wikipedia

Kazakh Wikipedia.label: Kazakh Wikipedia
Kazakh Wikipedia.description: The Kazakh Wikipedia is a Wikipedia in the Kazakh language. Wikipedia

WikiLeaks.label: WikiLeaks
WikiLeaks.description: WikiLeaks is an international, online, non-profit, journalistic organisation which publishes secret information, news leaks, and classified media from anonymous sources. Wikipedia
Awards: Amnesty International UK Digital Media Award

MathWorld.label: MathWorld
MathWorld.description: MathWorld is an online mathematics reference work, created and largely written by Eric W. Weisstein. Wikipedia

ImageShack.label: Imageshack
ImageShack.description: ImageShack is a paid-for image hosting website headquartered at Los Gatos, California. According to Nielsen//NetRatings, ImageShack was the fourth fastest growing web brand in July 2006. Wikipedia

Kongregate.label: Kongregate
Kongregate.description: Kongregate is an online games hosting website owned by Gamestop Corporation, which allows users to upload user-created Adobe Flash, HTML 5/JavaScript, Shockwave, Java or Unity3D games. Users can rate the games and search games by its user rating. Wikipedia

German Wikipedia.label: German Wikipedia
German Wikipedia.description: The German Wikipedia is the German-language edition of Wikipedia, a free and publicly editable online encyclopedia. Wikipedia

Orion's Arm.label: Orion's Arm
Orion's Arm.description: Orion's Arm, is a multi-authored online science fiction world-building project, first established in 2000 by M. Alan Kazlev, Donna Malcolm Hirsekorn, Bernd Helfert and Anders Sandberg and further co-authored by many people since. Wikipedia

Russian Wikipedia.label: Russian Wikipedia
Russian Wikipedia.description: The Russian Wikipedia is the Russian language edition of Wikipedia. It has over 1,094,000 articles. It was founded on 20 May 2001. By May 2008 it had become the 10th largest Wikipedia by size and in January 2014 it ranks 7th. Wikipedia

Technorati.label: Technorati
Technorati.description: Technorati is an Internet search engine for searching blogs. By June 2008, Technorati was indexing 112.8 million blogs and over 250 million pieces of tagged social media. Wikipedia

Softonic.com.label: Softonic International S.L.
Softonic.com.description: Softonic.com is a software download portal based in Barcelona, Spain, founded in 1997. Since 2007, the portal has included a blog called OnSoftware. Wikipedia

Aluka.label: Aluka
Aluka.description: Aluka is an online digital library focusing on materials about Africa. Aluka's mission is to connect scholars from around the world by building a common platform that allows online collaboration and knowledge sharing. Wikipedia

GittiGidiyor.label: Gittigidiyor
GittiGidiyor.description: GittiGidiyor, a subsidiary of eBay, is a Turkish e-shopping mall. The company's URL comes from the Turkish translation of "Going, going, gone". GittiGidiyor offers a wide variety of products, similar to the main eBay website. Wikipedia

Truthout.label: Truthout
Truthout.description: Truthout is a 501 nonprofit, progressive news organization in the United States that operates a web site and distributes a daily newsletter. Wikipedia
